            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">69. A 27 year old female presents with an acute blindness in her right eye after having a major argument with her boyfriend. In the ED she is found to deny physical trauma to the eye but she insists she cannot see anything out of her right eye. In spite of this, she is not particularly concerned about her monocular blindness but notes that it has happened before after fighting with her boyfriend. The ED physician notes that her right eye is normal looking and reacts to light normally. What is the most likely diagnosis?</p>"
